The paper deals with algorithms for performing computations on huge random objects, specifically undirected graphs with independent edge probabilities, random Catalan objects, and uniformly random valid q-colorings of an input graph. These topics are closely related to data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT).
